<package>
  <metadata>
    <id>HttpErrorMvc</id>
    <version>$version$</version>
    <title>NotFound MVC</title>
    <authors>efenghuo</authors>
    <owners>efenghuo</owners>
    <description>
      forked from NotFoundMVC owned by Andrew Davey, David De Sloovere.
      Provides a user-friendly '404' or any other http error page whenever a controller, action or route is not found in your ASP.NET MVC3/MVC4/MVC5 application.
      A view(default named Error) is rendered instead of the default ASP.NET error page.
    </description>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/andrewdavey/notfoundmvc</projectUrl>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php</licenseUrl>
    <iconUrl>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/andrewdavey/NotFoundMvc/master/package/logo.png</iconUrl>
    <tags>asp.net mvc notfound 404</tags>
    <language>en-US</language>
    <releaseNotes>
v1.5: Async controller support (added by mortan)
v1.4: Improved view, don't blown up when attribute routing is enabled, hook for an action to log 404s yourself
v1.3: Play nice with Glimpse (no exception if 404 with Glimpse installed)
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="..\..\package\content\**\*.*" target="content" />
